5:
Heh-heh-heh! I am Inaho Tamamo,
daughter of the world-spanning
Nine Tails!
9:
Ahahaha... And I am Lumira, ruler of
the abyssal night!
21: Oh! You two are perfect together!
25:
A collaboration between fox and
vampire! It was Lumira's idea!
30:
Heh-heh... I practiced a lot for this,
and I think I did pretty well!
35:
Oh, come on, Simon. Why didn't you
tell me such a lovely girl was living in
the castle?
41:
Heehee... Hey, Prika. You should join
us next!
49:
Are you not worried about that
anymore?
54:
D-don't worry, Yuki! Even without any
followers, I'm doing fine!
57:
You've all become my friends, so I'm
not lonely at all!
62:
Today was so much fun! I'm really
glad I came here.
65:
...But I hope I didn't... go overboard,
or anything...
69:
"Heehee"? Did I really laugh like
that?! It probably sounded awful
coming from me! They're gonna
think I'm a total weirdo!
73:
Ugh... Whenever somebody talked to
me, just responding was hard!
76:
If I wasn't a vampire and was just
the same as everybody else... I
wonder if they'd understand me
better...
83:
B-behold, I am Lumira of the abyssal
night! You will join me tonight... As
my eternal follower!
90:
...M-maybe descending from a high
place first is too scary!
94:
Kinda nuts that the Guild Knights
have gotta do patrols so late. It's
gotta be rough.
97:
No, it's actually pretty fun. The shift's
about to end, too—
106:
B-but... You won't be able to die
anymore, you know? The sun will
irritate your skin, and you might lose
your memories, too!
109:
Heh. That's fine. I've spent enough
time busting my ass in the
Kaleidoscope. I'm ready for another
life.
110:
I'm fine with all the conditions you
laid out. Go ahead—suck my blood.
117:
It's a contract stating that you're
going to become my follower.
Agreement, understanding, and
commitment. All super important,
right?
120:
Make sure you check page 27! It's
got a list of foods you'll dislike as a
vampire, common bloodsucking
dreams, and also—
123:
Mm, hmm... Looks like this is gonna
be harder than I was expecting.
Guess I'll pass this time...
126:
I-I understand. I hope you'll give it
some further thought! I'll be waiting!
130:
Th-that's only fourteen rejections so
far! I can do this! Just gotta call out
to the next person...
138: Hey. Have you had dinner yet?
142:
"146 Commitments for a Follower."
Huh? Are you really trying to get
people to sign a contract?
146:
I-it's because it's something they
can't go back on later! I don't want
either of us to have any regrets!
150:
Maybe you could just gobble
someone up entirely and not worry
about the whole follower thing.
153:
Might be worth a shot. I'm sure you
could find people who'd be into that.
157: I-I couldn't do something like that!
161:
Then I guess you've gotta give up. If
you're gonna be so wound up like
this, even holding someone's hand
is too much to expect.
166:
B-but... I'm just not the same as
everyone else. I easily lose track of
what's going on...
169:
But if they're my follower... If we're
the same, then we'll definitely...
175:
...I wonder if you'd really be able to
understand each other if you were
the "same."
183:
Whether we're the same or different,
I feel like there will always be times
when we can't understand another...
190:
Do you also think in circles when
you're with other people?
194:
Um... I guess I do. But again, that's
just how I do things.
196: But I decided I'm okay with that.
200:
...Then that's okay. Even if we're not
the same...
204:
I-I... still want to know more about
Inaho and the others, too! What
should I do?
209:
Huh? So you just wanna get to know
them better after all?
213:
Ah... I-I do, but I don't think I can give
up on having followers, either!
218:
...I see. I guess that's just who you
are, then.
227:
Woww. Wowww! My skin's not itchy
at all!
230:
Parasols are amazing! Now I can
have fun with everybody even when
it's bright out!
234:
Just don't overdo it by trying to get
close to everybody all at once
236:
How about you try getting to know
me a little better first?
243:
I'll keep doing my best! When I finally
get a follower someday, I'll be sure
to introduce you two!
247:
...Hey, when you create a follower...
What does it feel like?
255:
Sorry. Was that a weird thing to ask?
I just wanted to know if you didn't
mind telling me.
258: Oh, uh... Right. I can tell you, Yuki...
261:
...If you don't mind, would you tell me
more about yourself too?
265: Of course. Let's chat for a while.
